                   <h1 class="box-title">Shari'a Rating Scale and Definations</h1>
                       <br/>
 
                       <p>IIRA uses a scale of AAA (sq) to B (SQ) to rate Shari'a Quality Compliance with AAA (sq) being the highest possible rating and B (SQ) being the lowest possible rating.</p><br />
                       <p>• AAA (sq) – In IIRA’s opinion, an entity/instrument rated AAA (sq) conforms to highest level of standards of Shari’a requirements in all aspects of Shari’a quality analysis.</p><br />
                       <p>• AA (sq) – In IIRA’s opinion, an entity/instrument rated AA (sq) conforms to very high level of standards of Shari’a requirements in all aspects of Shari’a quality analysis.</p><br />
                       <p>• A (sq) – In IIRA’s opinion, an entity/instrument rated A (sq) conforms to high level of standards of Shari’a requirements and has very few weaknesses in some areas of Shari’a quality analysis.</p><br />
                       <p>• BBB (sq) – In IIRA’s opinion, an entity/instrument rated BBB (sq) conforms to moderately high level of standards of Shari’a requirements and has few weaknesses in some areas of Shari’a quality analysis.</p><br />
                       <p>• BB (sq) – In IIRA’s opinion, an entity/instrument rated BB (sq) conforms to satisfactory level of standards of Shari’a requirements and has some weaknesses in some areas of Shari’a quality analysis.</p><br />
                       <p>• B (sq) – In IIRA’s opinion, an entity/instrument rated B (sq) conforms to adequate level of standards of Shari’a requirements and has weaknesses in some areas of Shari’a quality analysis.</p><br /><br />
			<p><strong>Note: </strong>IIRA appends modifiers + or - to each generic rating classification from AA through B. The modifier + indicates that the obligation ranks in the higher end of its generic rating category; no modifier indicates a mid-range ranking; and the modifier - indicates a ranking in the lower end of that generic rating category.</p><br />
